1. Definitions
Restricted Content
  Any source files or directories (and any files or directories in said directories, and so on) listed (or described with the '*' wildcard) in the accompanying RESTRICTED-CONTENT file, as well as object files compiled from such source files. In absence of a RESTRICTED-CONTENT file, all of the Software is Restricted Content.
Compete
  Any project providing the same or similar functionality as the Software, targeting the same or a similar user base, is said to Compete with the Software. This includes, but is not limited to, any project that directly substitutes functionality of the Software.
Official Sources
  Any distribution channel through which the author(s) release(s) copies of the Software.
